body:
**Description**

I am creating a Lottie animation in my MAUI app, and it works correctly targeting Windows, but when I target Android, I get the exception:  "Method not found: System.TimeSpan SkiaSharp.Skottie.Animation.get_Duration()'"

**Code**

var stream = await FileSystem.OpenAppPackageFileAsync(Source);
string data = (new System.IO.StreamReader(stream)).ReadToEnd();
// load Lottie animation
SkiaSharp.Skottie.Animation.TryParse(data, out animation);

// Read important values
var duration = animation.Duration.TotalSeconds;

**Expected Behavior**

Work the same on Android as it does Windows

**Actual Behavior**

When I remove the reference to animation.Duration, I don't get the exception, but the app crashes when it tries to parse the animation json data.

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  2.88.1
- IDE:  Visual Studio
- Platform Target Frameworks: 
  - Android: <!-- the version of the Android SDK you are compiling against, e.g. 7.1 --> 
  - Target Devices:   Samsung S21 Ultra
